{{groovy}}
doc.use("MailArchiveCode.SettingsClass")
println """{{html wiki="true"}}
<form class="xform" name="settingsform">
<dl>"""
xwiki.getClass('MailArchiveCode.SettingsClass').getEnabledPropertyNames().each { prop ->
  println """<dt><label for="input_id_${prop}">${doc.displayPrettyName(prop)}</label></dt>
  <dd>${doc.display(prop)}</dd>"""
}
println """</dl>
</form>
{{/html}}"""
{{/groovy}}


{{info}}Mail folder should target a folder in your server mailbox, accessible with defined account. This folder should contain all mails you want to manage in the mailing-list Archive application. The tool will load non-read mails, and set them as read once loaded. To re-load mails, just change their flag in your folder.{{/info}}

